news.title: In six months, Mysuru development body recovers property worth Rs 533 crore
news.para: Muda has reclaimed over 54.25 acres of prime land and 134 sites in six months which were either being encroached or illegally occupied by people from several years.

news.title: Chennai: Revenue through property registration at a five-year high
news.para: The 2021 April to December revenue was 43% more than in 2020 (6,881 crore) and 19% more than the pre-Covid year of 2019 (8,267 crore). Registration department sources said the revenue is likely to touch 15,000 crore by end of March, 2022.

news.title: Mumbai: Flat owners lick wounds as fake army officers invade bank accounts
news.para: ​The police and cybercrime experts have warned flat owners to watch out before initiating a transaction and have urged them to try their best to check the credentials of those who approach them for renting apartments.

news.title: Tenants sans flats for 42 years, can't nix allotment on whim: Bombay HC
news.para: The allotment was made four decades after a dilapidated building he resided in was demolished. The building at Temkar Street in south Mumbai was demolished in 1978.

news.title: Hosur now gets development authority
news.para: The government had proposed to constitute urban development authorities for Coimbatore, Tirupur, Madurai and Hosur in the 2021-22 budget.

news.title: Greater Noida development body improves its finances with recoveries, schemes
news.para: The financial health of development bodies in Gautam Budh Nagar, mainly Noida Authority and GNIDA, has been under stress because of large dues accrued by realtors against land allotment.

news.title: River sand mining set to return in Tamil Nadu
news.para: To begin with, the department of water resources permitted 16 lorry quarries and 21 bullock carts’ sand quarries, which had environmental clearance (EC), to operate.

news.title: New MahaRERA rule will help home buyers be updated on project status
news.para: Developers required to provide certificates from engineers, CAs to banks, MahaRERA before withdrawing home allottees’ money

news.title: Mumbai: Ten years on, 197 buyers of Oshiwara flats file Rs 70 crore cheating case
news.para: Meanwhile, the builder, Jayesh Thokarsi Shah of Ravi Group, is currently lodged in Arthur Road jail following his arrest in another case by the Mumbai Economic Offences Wing (EOW) last month for allegedly cheating five, who had booked flats in his other project, Evershine Cosmic, of Rs 10 crore.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's sales bookings jump two-fold to Rs 1,965 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Its sales bookings rose to Rs 1,965 crore during the October-December quarter from Rs 971 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Government approves six town planning schemes in three cities of Gujarat
news.para: The two preliminary TP schemes approved by Patel include TP Scheme No. 429 (Godhavi-Manipur) under Auda in Ahmedabad and TP Scheme No. 71 (Vadod) of Surat Municipal Corporation.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group pressured by local government to repay wealth product investors
news.para: Kwok Ying Shing, chairman of the cash-strapped developer, has agreed to a request from the government of Shenzhen where the company is based, to provide by the end of January a proposal to repay investors in its wealth management products (WMPs), said one of the sources.

news.title: Mysuru civic body to start B khatas for illegal buildings
news.para: The MCC, which collects around Rs 160 crore in taxes, can hope to collect Rs 30 crore to Rs 60 crore more once these 50,000 properties are brought under taxation.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes illegal portions of four buildings in Chikitsak Nagar
news.para: Continuing its crackdown against illegal constructions, Indore Municipal Corporation (IMC) on Friday demolished portions of four buildings in Chikitsak Nagar that were developed on permission of residential use but were operating as hotels there.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco includes 32 villages in Khopta New Town development
news.para: ​The new township involves 32 revenue villages encompassing Panvel and Uran talukas. This area includes 7 villages from Panvel tehsil of the Raigad district and 25 villages from the Uran tehsil.
